  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "Caramelize the chopped onions in butter until golden brown.",
    "Add the chopped carrots and celery to the pot and cook until tender.",
    "Add the diced potatoes, chicken broth, and milk to the pot and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat and let simmer for 15 minutes or until the potatoes are tender.",
    "Add the fermented haddock fillets to the pot and cook for an additional 5 minutes.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a baking dish and top with crispy breadcrumbs.",
    "Bake in the preheated oven for 10 minutes or until the top is golden brown."
